# LaunchPe — Environment Variables Setup
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: Never commit real keys to Git!
# Add these in Netlify Dashboard:
# Site settings → Environment variables → Add variable
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

# Groq API Key (get from console.groq.com/keys)
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO ADD IN NETLIFY:
# 1. Go to app.netlify.com → your site
# 2. Site configuration → Environment variables
# 3. Click "Add a variable"
# 4. Key: GROQ_API_KEY
# 5. Value: your actual key
# 6. Click Save
# 7. Redeploy your site
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# The Groq key is NEVER in any frontend file.
# It lives only in Netlify's secure env vars.
# The analyze.js and regenerate.js functions
# read it via process.env.GROQ_API_KEY
